.TH "dbg_chk_lpt_sz" 9 "dbg_chk_lpt_sz" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dbg_chk_lpt_sz \- check LPT does not write more than LPT size.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dbg_chk_lpt_sz
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "int action "  ","
.BI "int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
the UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "action" 12
what to do
.IP "len" 12
length written
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns 0 on success and a negative error code on failure.
The \fIaction\fP argument may be one of:
o 0 - LPT debugging checking starts, initialize debugging variables;
o 1 - wrote an LPT node, increase LPT size by \fIlen\fP bytes;
o 2 - switched to a different LEB and wasted \fIlen\fP bytes;
o 3 - check that we've written the right number of bytes.
o 4 - wasted \fIlen\fP bytes;
